# Munciana Drills folder — deferred ingest

**Date deferred:** 2026-04-24
**Task:** Tracks 1+2 plan Task 3.2 (`docs/superpowers/plans/2026-04-24-wiki-improvement-tracks-1-2.md`)

## Contents
Single file: `2022MuncianaCampDrills.mp4` (1.35 GB video recording of 2022 Munciana Volleyball Camp drill sessions).

## Reason deferred
The folder contains only a binary video file. Converting the video to text requires transcription tooling that is not available in this session:
- No `ffmpeg` on PATH (needed to extract audio)
- No local `whisper` / faster-whisper / speech-to-text binary on PATH
- The `mcp__aoc__aoc_video_transcript` MCP tool only fetches transcripts for AOC-hosted (Vimeo/Wistia) videos, not local MP4 files
- No paired notes, slide deck, session outline, or drill write-up accompanies the video in the folder

Per SCHEMA §9 anti-patterns ("never fabricate citations"), drill pages cannot be created without actually observing the content. Guessing drill names, setups, or coaching points from the filename alone would fabricate material attributed to Munciana / Mike Lingenfelter.

## Research hypothesis for future ingest
When transcription tooling is available (e.g., local `whisper` install, paid transcription service, or an AOC-hosted version of this session is surfaced):
1. Transcribe full video → `raw/transcripts/munciana-2022-camp-drills.md` with timestamps
2. Create `wiki/sources/munciana-2022-camp-drills.md` (Tier 1 for club-hosted primary source; Tier 2 if processed through AOC)
3. For each discrete drill shown, author `wiki/drills/munciana-<slug>.md` per SCHEMA §3.7 with `sources: [munciana-2022-camp-drills]` and inferred `techniques:` / `primary-skill:` / `phase:` / `levels:` / `team-size-*` / `duration-min` / `equipment:` fields
4. If ≥5 drills land, add a `## Munciana drill cluster` section to `wiki/schools/munciana-volleyball-club.md` with wikilinks to each new drill
5. Cross-link new drills from `wiki/coaches/mike-lingenfelter.md` under a new `## Camp drill corpus` subsection of Contributions

## Tracks 1+2 acceptance criterion
The Dispatch 3 success criterion "Munciana Drills/ folder is fully committed or explicitly deferred with a log note" is satisfied by the log entry in `wiki/log.md` dated 2026-04-24 (defer | Munciana Drills). This `.deferred` marker carries the full research hypothesis so a later session can execute the ingest without re-diagnosing why the original attempt stopped.
